.TH "fscrypt_new_context" 9 "fscrypt_new_context" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fscrypt_new_context \- create a new fscrypt_context
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fscrypt_new_context
.BI "(union fscrypt_context *ctx_u "  ","
.BI "const union fscrypt_policy *policy_u "  ","
.BI "const u8 nonce[FSCRYPT_FILE_NONCE_SIZE] "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx_u" 12
output context
.IP "policy_u" 12
input policy
.IP "nonce" 12
nonce to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create an fscrypt_context for an inode that is being assigned the given
encryption policy.  \fInonce\fP must be a new random nonce.
.SH "RETURN"
the size of the new context in bytes.
